# <subsystem>: <brief description (50 chars or less)
>
# Example: sched: add priority scheduling support
# Example: mm: fix buddy allocator coalescing bug

# Provide more detailed explanation (if needed)
# Wrap lines at 72 characters

# Subsystem prefixes you can use:
# kernel  - Main kernel initialization and core
# sched   - Task scheduler and multitasking
# mm      - Memory management (pmm, kmalloc, paging)
# graphics - Display and graphics output
# time    - Timer and timing functions
# cpu     - CPU-specific code (IDT, GDT, interrupts)
# lib     - Utility libraries and helpers
# build   - Build system and Makefiles
# docs    - Documentation
# test    - Test code and test fixes
# misc    - General or uncategorized changes

# Remember to:
# - Keep subject line concise and clear
# - Use present tense ("add" not "added", "fix" not "fixed")
# - Explain the 'why', not just the 'what'